Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 07:06:32 +0200
Subject: [slayzone] slayzone: Phase 16.4 local-only crash sink
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Installs SIGSEGV/SIGABRT/SIGBUS/SIGILL handlers in the browser
process that write JSON stack traces to <user-data-dir>/crashes/.
Replaces the Crashpad upload stripped in Phase 2.4 — local file
only, no network. Sidecar HTTP forwarding deferred to Phase 19.

The handler is async-signal-safe (open/write/_exit + backtrace_symbols_fd).
Install() pre-composes the JSON prefix (version, userDataDir) so the
handler just appends signum + timestamp + backtrace.

--slayzone-test-crash switch triggers CHECK(false) immediately so the
sink can be exercised from the run script. Verified end-to-end:
run.sh -- --slayzone-test-crash produces crash-<ts>-<sig>.json with
version, userDataDir, signal number, timestamp, and backtrace.
